description.narrative: The project development objective is to (i) contribute to GOE's program of switching consumption of liquefied petroleum gas (LPG) for natural gas through investment in new connections; and (ii) exploit the scale economies in transportation of natural gas relative to LPG in very densely populated areas, thereby reducing the cost of gas provision.

title.narrative: Annual number of new connections achieved compared to plan

comment.narrative: As end of September 2012, a total of 358,862 new connections have been made and converted in 3 years since the project becameeffective in March 2009. This compares with the targeted total of 287,500 in the first 3 years.

title.narrative: Annual Savings from reduced subsidies for LPG (LE and US$/year)

comment.narrative: The annual saving is estimated for 10/01/2011-09/30/2011) based on the progressing connection of the more than 330,000 newhouseholds so far. Those households converted before April 1, 2011 used gas for the full year. Those households converted afterApril 1,2011used gas only for part of the year. So the estimation is very rough.

title.narrative: Reduction of LPG consumption in the target area (ton/year)

comment.narrative: The avoided consumption of 80,000 tons is estimated for the one year period (10/01/2011-09/30/2012). This compares with the targetof 72,450 tons for year 1 in the PAD. But the estimation is very rough as the households are converted progressively and there arenew households switching to gas everyday.
